-- ON THE MOVE-Fiduciary 'study group' Zero Alpha Group adds new member
-- By Elizabeth Dilts
-- Wed Oct 22, 2014 04:11PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Oct 22 (Reuters) - Zero Alpha Group, a professional club of eight registered investment advisors (RIAs) that operates like a "study group" for fiduciary financial advisers, said Wednesday it added its first new member in eight years.

TCI Wealth Advisors, based in Tucson, Arizona, is one of the largest RIAs in the U.S. West and Southwest with more than $1.6 billion in client assets under management.